{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/2017-10-17-api-first-and-the-customer-experience","webpackCompilationHash":"2ff2dae5022005648504","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"kevinhakanson.com","author":"Kevin Hakanson"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"ae870d24-064a-5125-8a55-17f7d3d0c054","excerpt":"Enabling distributed digital business with API-first architecture (Google Cloud Next ‘17) was a good, high-level overview of API strategies, and reminds me of…","html":"<p><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9SmXhbgYmbU\">Enabling distributed digital business with API-first architecture (Google Cloud Next ‘17)</a> was a good, high-level overview of API strategies, and reminds me of our internal Customer Experience Model and Customer Experience Principles goals.</p>\n<p>The “Inside-out” vs. “Outside-in” perspective is analogous to how developers used to build UIs, but we now utilize a Central UX: Experience Design &#x26; Research team to focus on the user (vs. the feature).</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 590px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/d20d62956ab9b1628a5723c1e310eeb2/fa92b/pastedImage_2.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 32.14285714285714%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"&quot;Inside-out&quot; - service provider view\"\n        title=\"&quot;Inside-out&quot; - service provider view\"\n        src=\"/static/d20d62956ab9b1628a5723c1e310eeb2/b9e4f/pastedImage_2.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/d20d62956ab9b1628a5723c1e310eeb2/cf440/pastedImage_2.png 148w,\n/static/d20d62956ab9b1628a5723c1e310eeb2/d2d38/pastedImage_2.png 295w,\n/static/d20d62956ab9b1628a5723c1e310eeb2/b9e4f/pastedImage_2.png 590w,\n/static/d20d62956ab9b1628a5723c1e310eeb2/f9b6a/pastedImage_2.png 885w,\n/static/d20d62956ab9b1628a5723c1e310eeb2/2d849/pastedImage_2.png 1180w,\n/static/d20d62956ab9b1628a5723c1e310eeb2/fa92b/pastedImage_2.png 1400w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 590px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/5d96200a9c1ed3635d83d9d2aa2b4b0b/fa92b/pastedImage_3.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 32.14285714285714%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"&quot;Outside-in&quot; - digital consumer view\"\n        title=\"&quot;Outside-in&quot; - digital consumer view\"\n        src=\"/static/5d96200a9c1ed3635d83d9d2aa2b4b0b/b9e4f/pastedImage_3.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/5d96200a9c1ed3635d83d9d2aa2b4b0b/cf440/pastedImage_3.png 148w,\n/static/5d96200a9c1ed3635d83d9d2aa2b4b0b/d2d38/pastedImage_3.png 295w,\n/static/5d96200a9c1ed3635d83d9d2aa2b4b0b/b9e4f/pastedImage_3.png 590w,\n/static/5d96200a9c1ed3635d83d9d2aa2b4b0b/f9b6a/pastedImage_3.png 885w,\n/static/5d96200a9c1ed3635d83d9d2aa2b4b0b/2d849/pastedImage_3.png 1180w,\n/static/5d96200a9c1ed3635d83d9d2aa2b4b0b/fa92b/pastedImage_3.png 1400w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>APIs serve different purposes, and your internal APIs might not be the SDKs or “experience APIs” the external developer needs.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>APIs as services (e.g. Web)</li>\n<li>APIs as interactions (e.g. Mobile or Partners)</li>\n<li>APIs as products (e.g. Devices)</li>\n</ul>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 590px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/7c0a6179c17de40fc2b2c93735a93843/de411/pastedImage_6.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 44.08060453400503%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"API layers\"\n        title=\"API layers\"\n        src=\"/static/7c0a6179c17de40fc2b2c93735a93843/b9e4f/pastedImage_6.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/7c0a6179c17de40fc2b2c93735a93843/cf440/pastedImage_6.png 148w,\n/static/7c0a6179c17de40fc2b2c93735a93843/d2d38/pastedImage_6.png 295w,\n/static/7c0a6179c17de40fc2b2c93735a93843/b9e4f/pastedImage_6.png 590w,\n/static/7c0a6179c17de40fc2b2c93735a93843/f9b6a/pastedImage_6.png 885w,\n/static/7c0a6179c17de40fc2b2c93735a93843/2d849/pastedImage_6.png 1180w,\n/static/7c0a6179c17de40fc2b2c93735a93843/de411/pastedImage_6.png 1588w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>The “mediation layer” above is where an API Gateway fits in, and where many of the non-functional requirements can be addressed.</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"API-First and the Customer Experience","date":"October 17, 2017","tags":["api"]}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/2017-10-17-api-first-and-the-customer-experience","previous":{"fields":{